          "question": "<p><a name=\"2045\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p><strong>Answer the questions on the basis of the information given below.</strong><br>\nThe seven basic symbols in a certain numeral system and their respective values are as follows:<br>\n\\( \\text{I} = 1, \\text{V} = 5, \\text{X} = 10, \\text{L} = 50, \\text{C} = 100, \\text{D} = 500, \\text{and M} = 1000 \\)<br>\nIn general, the symbols in the numeral system are read from left to right, starting with the symbol representing the largest value; the same symbol cannot occur continuously more than three times; the value of the numeral is the sum of the values of the symbols. For example, \\( \\text{XXVII} = 10 + 10 + 5 + 1 + 1 = 27. \\) An exception to the left-to-right reading occurs when a symbol is followed immediately by a symbol of greater value; then, the smaller value is subtracted from the large. For example, \\( \\text{XLVI} = (50 – 10) + 5 + 1 = 46. \\)</p>\n\n<p><br>\nWhich of the following can represent the numeral for \\( 1995? \\)</p>\n\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-alpha\">\n\t<li>MCMLXXV</li>\n\t<li>MCMXCV</li>\n\t<li>MVD</li>\n\t<li>MVM\n\t\n\t</li>\n</ol></div><br><br><b>Logical Reasoning: CAT 2003 | Question: 2</b></p>",
